  "text": "A recent study of the incidence and prevalence of CP in Olmstead County, USA, made use of unusual arrangements for the provision of medical care in its methodology. [CITATION_1] In this US county, nearly all medical care is provided by a central hospital (renowned for keeping large longitudinal databases of patient records) and a single primary care centre. This permits more complete capture of epidemiological data than it is possible in the gastroenterologist-gatekeeper scenario. Interestingly, this study provided estimates of incidence (4.05/100,000) and prevalence (41.8/100,000), more in line with longevity estimates for patients with CP.",
